---
title: Rosemary Pork Chops with Mashed Potatoes, Brussel Sprouts & Pan Sauce
description: These, friends, are not your average pork chops. Our chefs gave ’em a steak-like treatment, transforming the everyday protein into something above and beyond. The chops are seared to perfection, then drizzled with an ultra-savory, rosemary-flecked pan sauce. The sides? Just as impressive. We’re serving up creamy mashed potatoes and roasted brussels sprouts and red onion wedges to round everything out.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64a4f7661f082ea356572cf5-71c7f1d1.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64a4f7661f082ea356572cf5.pdf
time required: 40 minutes
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
course: main course
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/rosemary-pork-chops-64a4f7661f082ea356572cf5
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 34 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 650 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and cut @Red Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss Brussels sprouts and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

> For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer pork to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Return #pot{} with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide pork, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top pork with sauce and serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.